                            <comment id="12604535" author="fpj" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2008 16:14:25 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;This is a tentative patch to fix the problems pointed out on QuorumPeer and FastLeaderElection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1- Makes logicalclock volatile;&lt;br/&gt;
2- Creates accessor methods for currentVote and state, and enforce their use;&lt;br/&gt;
3- Accessor methods are synchronized.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-F&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12604537" author="fpj" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2008 16:15:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Please check the attached patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12604645" author="evanj" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2008 22:22:01 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;A quick look at the patch looks good to me. However there is a &quot;long logicalclock&quot; in AuthFastLeaderElection.java as well. It looks like it should also be volatile.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
